  m_text: Apolinario Mabini was born on July 23, 1864, in Tanauan, Batangas, into
    a humble and poor family. Despite their limited resources, Mabini showed determination
    to pursue his education. He worked hard to support himself while studying, often
    facing financial struggles. Through perseverance, he was able to study at the
    University of Santo Tomas, where he earned a degree in law. Mabini became known
    for his sharp intellect, discipline, and strong sense of justice, which later
    shaped his role in the Philippine Revolution.
