      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Andres Bonifacio was born on November 30, 1863, in Tondo, Manila. Unlike
    other heroes, he did not come from a wealthy or highly educated family. After
    the death of his parents, Bonifacio had to stop studying and worked hard to support
    his younger siblings. Despite this, he educated himself by reading books about
    history, law, and the French Revolution. Through his experiences and self-learning,
    he developed a strong sense of patriotism and a desire to fight against injustice.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
