  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: He strongly believed that freedom should not only be achieved but also
    properly managed through a just and disciplined government. Mabini opposed corruption
    and warned against leaders who sought personal power instead of national progress.
    Even when he was captured and exiled by the Americans, he remained firm in his
    principles and refused to compromise his beliefs. Today, Apolinario Mabini is
    remembered as a symbol of wisdom, integrity, and dedication to the Filipino nation.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2140474, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
