      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Lapu-Lapu was a powerful chieftain of Mactan, Cebu, who lived during the
    early 16th century. He is known as one of the first Filipino heroes to resist
    foreign colonization. During this time, Spanish explorers, led by Ferdinand Magellan,
    arrived in the Philippines and began forming alliances with local rulers. While
    some leaders accepted Spanish authority, Lapu-Lapu chose to defend his land and
    people, refusing to submit to foreign control.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2140474, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
