      m_Calls: []
  m_text: When the Philippine Revolution and later the Philippine-American War began,
    Luna became one of the most skilled and disciplined military leaders of the Filipino
    forces. He served as a general and was known for his strict leadership, strong
    strategies, and desire to build a well-trained and organized army. He introduced
    military systems such as defensive trenches and strategic planning to strengthen
    the Filipino resistance. However, his strict personality caused conflicts with
    other soldiers and leaders.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2140474, guid: 8a89fa14b10d46a99122fd4f73fca9a2, type: 2}
